Claim status by verification status¶

In [82]:
pink = '#FFB6C1'
blue = '#336699'
orange = '#FFA500'
In [121]:
plt.figure(figsize=(7, 4))
sns.histplot(data=df, x='claim_status', hue='verified_status',
             multiple="dodge", shrink=0.9,
             palette=[pink, blue])
plt.title("Distribution by Claim and Verification Status")
plt.show()
  • Verified users post more videos with opinions than with claims. Unverified users post more videos with claims than with opinions. This discrepancy is higher in verified users.

Claim status by author ban status¶

In [124]:
sns.histplot(data=df, x='claim_status', hue='author_ban_status',
             multiple="dodge", shrink=0.9,
             hue_order=['active', 'under review', 'banned'],
             palette=[pink, blue, orange])
plt.title("Distribution by Claim and Author Ban Status")
plt.show()

  • Claims:

    • under review and banned have similar counts
    • active count is much highter

  • Opinions:

    • under review count is roughly 2x more than banned count
    • active count is highest out of all categories

Total views by claim status¶

In [103]:
total_views = df.groupby('claim_status')['video_view_count'].sum()

plt.figure(figsize=(4, 4))
plt.pie(total_views, labels=total_views.index, autopct='%1.1f%%',
        colors=[pink, blue])  # Using the colorblind friendly palette
plt.title("Proportions of Total Views by Claim Status")
plt.show()
  • Although there is a relatively equal proportion of claim and opinion videos, 99% of views go to claim videos

Determine outliers¶

In [132]:
cols = list(df.columns)[7:]
In [133]:
for column in cols:
    Q1 = df[column].quantile(0.25)
    Q3 = df[column].quantile(0.75)

    IQR = Q3 - Q1
    median = df[column].median()

    outlier_threshold = median + 1.5*IQR
    outlier_count = (df[column] > outlier_threshold).sum()
    print(f"Number of outliers, {column}: {outlier_count}")

Number of outliers, video_view_count: 2343
Number of outliers, video_like_count: 3468
Number of outliers, video_share_count: 3732
Number of outliers, video_download_count: 3733
Number of outliers, video_comment_count: 3882

Conclusion¶

  • All of the engangement statistics are heavily right skewed, which is to be expected of TikTok data - few videos tend to go viral and receive very high engagement.
  • Video view count might be a good indicator of claim status.
